fields.name: Electronic Dance Music
fields.description: Electronic Dance Music, also known as EDM, is a broad term encompassing various genres. It's typically characterized by strong beats, rhythmic pulses, and electronic instruments.

fields.name: Indie Rock
fields.description: Indie rock is a genre of alternative rock music that originated in the United States and the United Kingdom during the 1980s and became widely popular in the 2000s.

fields.name: Hip Hop
fields.description: Hip hop is a cultural movement that originated in the 1970s in the Bronx, New York City, and includes elements like rapping, DJing, breakdancing, and graffiti.

fields.name: Jazz
fields.description: Jazz is a genre of music that originated in the African-American communities in New Orleans, Louisiana, around the beginning of the 20th century, characterized by swing and blue notes.

fields.name: Classical
fields.description: Classical music is a long-established tradition of music that spans over a thousand years, characterized by highly formalized structures and symphonic compositions.
